{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:luke.24",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "luke",
    "chapterNumber": 24,
    "referenceLabel": "Luke 24",
    "summary": "Source text for Luke 24 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:1",
      "text": "But on the first day of the week, at early dawn, they went to the tomb, taking the spices which they had prepared.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:2",
      "text": "And they found the stone rolled away from the tomb,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:3",
      "text": "but when they went in they did not find the body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:4",
      "text": "While they were perplexed about this, behold, two men stood by them in dazzling apparel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:5",
      "text": "and as they were frightened and bowed their faces to the ground, the men said to them, “Why do you seek the living among the dead?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:6",
      "text": "Remember how he told you, while he was still in Galilee,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:7",
      "text": "that the Son of man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and on the third day rise.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:8",
      "text": "And they remembered his words,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:9",
      "text": "and returning from the tomb they told all this to the eleven and to all the rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:10",
      "text": "Now it was Mary Magdalene and Jo-anna and Mary the mother of James and the other women with them who told this to the apostles;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:11",
      "text": "but these words seemed to them an idle tale, and they did not believe them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:13",
      "text": "That very day two of them were going to a village named Emmaus, about seven miles from Jerusalem,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:14",
      "text": "and talking with each other about all these things that had happened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:15",
      "text": "While they were talking and discussing together, Jesus himself drew near and went with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:16",
      "text": "But their eyes were kept from recognizing him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:17",
      "text": "And he said to them, “What is this conversation which you are holding with each other as you walk?” And they stood still, looking sad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:18",
      "text": "Then one of them, named Cleopas, answered him, “Are you the only visitor to Jerusalem who does not know the things that have happened there in these days?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:19",
      "text": "And he said to them, “What things?” And they said to him, “Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, who was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:20",
      "text": "and how our chief priests and rulers delivered him up to be condemned to death, and crucified him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:21",
      "text": "But we had hoped that he was the one to redeem Israel. Yes, and besides all this, it is now the third day since this happened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:22",
      "text": "Moreover, some women of our company amazed us. They were at the tomb early in the morning",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:23",
      "text": "and did not find his body; and they came back saying that they had even seen a vision of angels, who said that he was alive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:24",
      "text": "Some of those who were with us went to the tomb, and found it just as the women had said; but him they did not see.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:25",
      "text": "And he said to them, “O foolish men, and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:26",
      "text": "Was it not necessary that the Christ should suffer these things and enter into his glory?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:27",
      "text": "And beginning with Moses and all the prophets, he interpreted to them in all the scriptures the things concerning himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:28",
      "text": "So they drew near to the village to which they were going. He appeared to be going further,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:29",
      "text": "but they constrained him, saying, “Stay with us, for it is toward evening and the day is now far spent.” So he went in to stay with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:30",
      "text": "When he was at table with them, he took the bread and blessed, and broke it, and gave it to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:31",
      "text": "And their eyes were opened and they recognized him; and he vanished out of their sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:32",
      "text": "They said to each other, “Did not our hearts burn within us while he talked to us on the road, while he opened to us the scriptures?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:33",
      "text": "And they rose that same hour and returned to Jerusalem; and they found the eleven gathered together and those who were with them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:34",
      "text": "who said, “The Lord has risen indeed, and has appeared to Simon!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:35",
      "text": "Then they told what had happened on the road, and how he was known to them in the breaking of the bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:36",
      "text": "As they were saying this, Jesus himself stood among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:37",
      "text": "But they were startled and frightened, and supposed that they saw a spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:38",
      "text": "And he said to them, “Why are you troubled, and why do questionings rise in your hearts?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:39",
      "text": "See my hands and my feet, that it is I myself; handle me, and see; for a spirit has not flesh and bones as you see that I have.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:41",
      "text": "And while they still disbelieved for joy, and wondered, he said to them, “Have you anything here to eat?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:42",
      "text": "They gave him a piece of broiled fish,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:43",
      "text": "and he took it and ate before them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:44",
      "text": "Then he said to them, “These are my words which I spoke to you, while I was still with you, that everything written about me in the law of Moses and the prophets and the psalms must be fulfilled.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:45",
      "text": "Then he opened their minds to understand the scriptures,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:46",
      "text": "and said to them, “Thus it is written, that the Christ should suffer and on the third day rise from the dead,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:47",
      "text": "and that repentance and forgiveness of sins should be preached in his name to all nations, beginning from Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:48",
      "text": "You are witnesses of these things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:49",
      "text": "And behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you; but stay in the city, until you are clothed with power from on high.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:50",
      "text": "Then he led them out as far as Bethany, and lifting up his hands he blessed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:51",
      "text": "While he blessed them, he parted from them, and was carried up into heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.52",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:52",
      "text": "And they returned to Jerusalem with great joy,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.24.53",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 24:53",
      "text": "and were continually in the temple blessing God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
